docs.text: all the wacky characters voiced by celebrities and fantastically animated adventure sequences aren't going to hold anyone's interest unless there is an emotional core to hold it all together .

docs.text: not since disney's beauty & the beast has there been such a compelling animated film with interesting characters and drama that works .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the story of the romanov family , the rulers of russia , and their downfall begins the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: anastasia , one of the daughters , narrowly escapes the mad monk rasputin ( voiced by christopher lloyd ) with her grandmother ( voiced by angela landsbury ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but anastasia gets lost , and grows up with no memory of her royal origins .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the grandmother lives in paris , hoping to someday find her beloved anastasia , the only member of the family to survive the russian revolution .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a young woman named anya ( voiced by meg ryan ) runs across dimitri ( john cusack ) and vlad ( kelsey grammar ) , who are trying to put together a scheme to create an anastasia to fool the grandmother and get the reward money .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they pick anya to pose as their princes , and of course , it is soon revealed that anya is in fact the lost anastasia .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: dimitri realizes that he can never win her love as he is a commoner , and meanwhile , rasputin is not dead , and plots his revenge against the last romanov .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the plot is actually quite well structured .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there are a lot of complexities that may have to be explained to the kids later , but it moves along fast enough that they'll never have time to be bored .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: what this really means is that the adults won't be bored by it either .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is a great deal of banter between anya and dimitri that is very funny , and their relationship develops quite naturally as the film progresses .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is , of course , lots of comedy for the kids , including rasputin's pet bat , bartok ( hank azaria ) , who is easily the funniest thing in the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , the comical scenes never distract from the drama , but are worked into the plot almost seamlessly .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the animation is gorgeous - the characters seem to come to life through the talented animators .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: not since beauty & the beast have animated characters had so much life to them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even without the voices , they act .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the musical number in paris is a show-stopper , with some of the backgrounds rendered in an impressionist painting style .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as with all recent animated features , there are songs , however , these songs do more than just provide fodder for top-40 singers to get on the radio ( although there are three of them during the end credits ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the songs are all very catchy , and advance the plot , instead of just being showpieces ( except for the paris number , but that's so much fun , it's okay . . . ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i can't reccomend anastasia highly enough .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's a wonderful film that ranks right up there with other animated classics .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: kids and adults alike will enjoy it , and it's also nice to have a quality animated feature film from another studio besides disney .
docs.label: positive
